cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper presents an algorithm for grasp pose detection of transparent objects in clutter using plenoptic sensing. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for object detection and pose estimation. The algorithm also involves machine learning (cs.AI) for classification of graspable locations and optimization of grasp execution. The use of plenoptic sensing involves graphics (cs.GR) techniques for capturing and processing light field data. Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm involves statistical analysis (cs.LG) of experimental results.
